description:
&lt;p&gt;We require a dynamic, enthusiastic and motivated respiratory nurse specialist/long term oxygen practitioner to work as part of the home oxygen team in Northumberland and North Tyneside.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will provide a comprehensive assessment and review service with a focus on patient centred care to all people who require home oxygen therapy, in line with local and national strategies. You will be able to demonstrate appropriate clinical skills and knowledge and plan and organise a clinical case load on a daily basis. The majority of services will be provided in the community therefore driving is essential to the post. You will be required to take a clinical role in current research and audit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to participate in delivering our Hospital@Home service on a rotational basis this includes weekend working and on call services, as well as other respiratory services: including supported discharge, acute assessments and outpatient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent interpersonal and communication skills and an ability to foster positive relationships at all levels, including discussion and presentation of relevant information to senior staff / commissioners. You will be required to promote integration with the multidisciplinary team who participate in the care of patients who require home oxygen and actively build relationships with all members. Maintaining accurate records and data management as well as data analysis to contribute to service development will be required. You will provide specialist teaching to patients and staff across the Trust and community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Judith Moody&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputy Senior Nurse specialist/Lead Nurse for the Home Oxygen Service&lt;/p&gt;
